### Authentication Middleware Example

### ========================================
### Public Route - No Auth Required
### ========================================

GET http://localhost:3000/public

###

### ========================================
### Protected Routes - API Key Required
### Should return 401 Unauthorized
### ========================================

GET http://localhost:3000/protected

###

GET http://localhost:3000/api/users

###

### ========================================
### Protected Routes - With Valid API Key
### Should return 200 OK
### ========================================

GET http://localhost:3000/protected
X-API-Key: secret-key-123

###

GET http://localhost:3000/api/users
X-API-Key: secret-key-123

###

GET http://localhost:3000/api/orders
X-API-Key: secret-key-123

###

### ========================================
### Protected Routes - With Invalid API Key
### Should return 403 Forbidden
### ========================================

GET http://localhost:3000/protected
X-API-Key: wrong-key

###

### ========================================
### Admin Routes - Requires API Key + Admin Role
### Should return 403 Forbidden (no admin role)
### ========================================

GET http://localhost:3000/admin
X-API-Key: secret-key-123

###

GET http://localhost:3000/api/admin/stats
X-API-Key: secret-key-123

###

### ========================================
### Admin Routes - With API Key + Admin Role
### Should return 200 OK
### ========================================

GET http://localhost:3000/admin
X-API-Key: secret-key-123
X-User-Role: admin

###

GET http://localhost:3000/api/admin/stats
X-API-Key: secret-key-123
X-User-Role: admin

###

GET http://localhost:3000/api/admin/logs
X-API-Key: secret-key-123
X-User-Role: admin

###
